-- Miner Sherritt shuts out dissidents in board election
-- By Euan Rocha
-- Tue May 06, 2014 11:14AM EDT
-- None



TORONTO, May 6 (Reuters) - Canadian miner Sherritt International Corp's <S.TO> management board nominees were all elected at the company's shareholder meeting on Tuesday, and no dissident nominees won spots on the board after a months-long proxy fight.

